{
	"id": 931,
	"documentId": "s8f5hwrj4ajccha3a7pg857k",
	"name": "Gili Trawangan, Gili Meno and Gili Air",
	"slug": "gili-trawangan-gili-meno-and-gili-air",
	"intro": [
		{
			"type": "paragraph",
			"children": [
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "The three beautiful Gili islands, located in Indonesia between the islands of"
				},
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "Bali",
					"url": "https://lowcost-traveling.com/asie/bali/"
				},
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "and"
				},
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "Lombok",
					"url": "https://lowcost-traveling.com/asie/lombok/"
				},
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": ", are ideal spots for relaxation, fun, diving, snorkeling, and more. Coral reefs surround the islands, and at certain locations, turtles arrive daily, allowing you to observe them up close. No motorized vehicles are allowed on the islands, except for electric scooters, so you can either travel by horse-drawn carriages or bicycles. When you see the skinny ponies pulling carts full of tourists and their luggage, you might think walking is not a bad option. The islands aren’t very large (about 2 km in diameter), and you can walk around them easily."
				}
			]
		},
