					"type": "text",
					"text": ""
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"type": "paragraph",
			"children": [
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "But which island should you choose? If you are looking for a touristy place with vibrant nightlife, massages, restaurants, beach cinemas, or drinks, then definitely Gili Trawangan. Here, you can almost be certain of swimming with turtles. On the other hand, if you are seeking peace and don’t need tourist facilities, Gili Meno is the way to go. Gili Air is somewhere in between."
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"type": "paragraph",
			"children": [
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "The islands offer excellent snorkeling on the coral reefs. We recommend bringing your own snorkeling gear or renting it here, including fins, for a fee. You can also buy it locally. Due to significant low tides, we recommend water shoes or fins, which will help you get into the sea over sharp rocks and corals during low tide."
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"type": "paragraph",
			"children": [
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "It’s important to monitor the tides and plan your activities accordingly. Otherwise, you might find that the sea literally disappears in the afternoon, leaving you on the beach under the scorching sun without any way to cool off. The sea level can fluctuate by up to 3 meters, exposing the seabed for tens of meters. In some places, swimming becomes impossible, while in others, you can walk across the seabed and try to reach the water where it starts again. This is also where the coral reefs begin, which means that walking on them will damage them and most likely injure you, as they are very sharp. It’s not ideal. To monitor the tides, you can use the mobile app Gili Tides."
				}
			]
		},
