		},
		{
			"type": "heading",
			"level": 2,
			"children": [
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "Gili Trawangan",
					"url": "https://goo.gl/maps/XtijAtASiHyFLpxC8"
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"type": "paragraph",
			"children": [
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "The largest of the three islands, Gili Trawangan, is also the most touristy, with the most developed nightlife. It’s often referred to as the „Party Island.“ Beautiful beaches can be found all around the island."
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"type": "paragraph",
			"children": [
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "You can find beautiful coral reefs practically all around the island, just a few dozen meters from the shore."
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"type": "paragraph",
			"children": [
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "The northern part of the island is calm, with no large waves, making it perfect for snorkeling, and in the northeast, you can also spot sea turtles. The southern part is rough and more suitable for surfers. It’s also where you’ll find the island’s only hill, where you can go to watch the sunset. The western beaches offer a beautiful view of the sunset behind Bali and the Balinese volcano. The eastern part of the island is mostly the town area, filled with tourist shops, tour offers, massages, and the port. Every night near the port, there’s a night market where you can buy skewered meat or fresh fish for dinner. Prices are usually negotiable."
				}
			]
		},
