		},
		{
			"type": "paragraph",
			"children": [
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "The nightlife here is quite lively, locals are accommodating and welcomingand the beaches are cleaned regularly, which is a rarity in Indonesia."
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"type": "heading",
			"level": 2,
			"children": [
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "Gili Meno",
					"url": "https://goo.gl/maps/B5SYUji9LvkNWfCc8"
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"type": "paragraph",
			"children": [
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "The smallest and quietest of all the islands, Gili Meno is also the most expensive. People typically come here to spend their honeymoon, so instead of cheap hostels, expect romantic thatched cottages right on the beach. However, this luxury is still reasonably priced. Most parts of the island lack internet access, so accommodations may not include it. Free internet can be found on the eastern part of the island, where the town area (a few shops) and the harbor are located. The northern part of the island is peaceful and far from the mosque, which is especially pleasant in the morning, as no one will wake you up at five. Paths around the island are sandy trails, giving the island a calm and natural feel."
				}
			]
		},
