				}
			]
		},
		{
			"type": "paragraph",
			"children": [
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "In the north and northwest of the island, there are beautiful coral reefs, but you have to swim about 50 meters from the shore to see something (at high tide). Here, you can also observe sea turtles. On the eastern part of the island, there is one of the tourist attractions—underwater statues. You can dive near the beach to see the famous circle of human statues. The site is easy to find—lots of boats and people. In the water right by the statues, it feels like a shipwreck full of people, with everyone bumping into each other, pushing, and almost climbing over one another. You can easily swim here from the shore, but most people visit this spot as part of boat tours."
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"type": "paragraph",
			"children": [
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "The biggest waves are on the south side of the island, where the most beautiful beach starts and continues east towards the harbor. As you head east, the water calms down, and you can swim in the beautiful turquoise water. In the southeast, visit the turtle hatchery. Locals here incubate turtle eggs and protect them until they are big enough, releasing them into the sea after about six months. They do this to save as many as possible from predators. The turtles are released into the sea when they have a high chance of survival. Admission is free (the hatchery consists of a few tanks), but you can leave a donation."
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"type": "paragraph",
			"children": [
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "Inside the island, you will find a salt lake and a bird zoo."
				}
			]
		},
